The paper deals with designing hashing-based indexing schemes for dictionaries and multimaps, which are fundamental data structures in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses cache-oblivious algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions the Random Access Machine (RAM) model, which is a common model in theoretical computer science, indicating that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
